mp3-archive NEWS

===========================================================================
v20260608 (2026-06-08)
===========================================================================

The Android (KivyMD) app reaches feature parity with the desktop app.

New features (Android)
----------------------
- Online metadata: single-song MusicBrainz lookup with a per-candidate
  tag diff (current -> proposed); source selection (MusicBrainz / iTunes
  / 둘 다) with a keyword override; and batch tag auto-completion that
  steps through files missing a title or artist.
- Table (표) view: a fifth list mode showing selectable, sortable,
  horizontally-scrollable tag columns (drag the header to scroll, tap a
  header to sort, ⋮ > 표 컬럼 to choose columns).
- List sort menu (name / artist / title / date), theme toggle
  (system / light / dark), and an About dialog, grouped in a ⋮ overflow
  menu.
- The 자세히 dialog shows read-only file/stream info (size, duration,
  created/modified, sample rate, channels, bitrate) and now edits every
  embedded easy-tag, not just six.
- Incremental scan: picking a folder merges into the library and skips
  unchanged files; the refresh button forces a full re-read and prunes
  records for files missing under that folder.
- Playlist / queue: tap a song to enqueue+play, long-press 재생목록에
  추가 (or add all selected); the 재생 tab shows the queue with a
  now-playing highlight, per-row remove, prev/next, play modes
  (순차 / 한곡반복 / 전체반복 / 셔플), auto-advance at track end, and
  .list save / load (skipping missing files) / clear. The queue
  auto-scrolls to the playing track, and long-pressing a 트리 folder
  enqueues every file under it.
- Player controls: a volume slider (with mute), an interactive seek bar,
  and album art plus a 가사 / 재생목록 toggle on the 재생 tab. Tracks
  without embedded art show a default placeholder.
- Branded loading screen: a white screen with the app icon, name, and
  version.

Bug fixes / improvements (Android)
----------------------------------
- Playback time and the progress bar now advance: the Android audio
  provider's get_pos() returns 0, so elapsed time is tracked from the
  poll interval instead.
- HTTPS metadata fetch (MusicBrainz / iTunes) works under
  python-for-android via a bundled certifi CA bundle.
- Hardened many queue/player edge cases found by review: multi-select
  add, removing the currently-playing track, append-vs-replace prompt on
  load, shuffle no longer re-picks the current track, prev on a
  never-played queue, and tree-folder add after an app relaunch.
- About dialog and loading screen now show the dated NEWS version
  on-device: the version is baked from NEWS into a bundled module
  (src/app_version.py via assets/make_version.py) since NEWS itself is
  not packaged into the APK, replacing the old 1.0.0 fallback.

===========================================================================
v20260420 (2026-04-20)
===========================================================================

New features
------------
- Menu bar: added 파일 / 스캔 / 보기 / 도움말 menus covering all major
  actions with keyboard shortcuts (Ctrl+O, Ctrl+S, Ctrl+L, Ctrl+Q,
  F5, Ctrl+F5, Ctrl+T, F1)
- Tree view: root is now the configured music directory instead of the
  filesystem root, showing only the relevant subdirectory structure
- Tree view is now the default view on startup (was table)
- About dialog: now shows the app icon (assets/icon.png) instead of
  the generic information icon

Bug fixes / improvements
------------------------
- Playlist: double-clicking a different song now correctly clears the
  previous track's highlight before highlighting the new one
- Menu items: added QMenu::item padding so shortcut text no longer
  overlaps action labels in custom themes
- Tooltips: added 4px 8px padding to QToolTip in all themes (including
  system theme) for consistent spacing
- About: moved from toolbar '?' button to 도움말 > About mp3-archive
  menu entry (F1); dialog widened so the window title is not truncated
- About: fixed ImportError (QSizePolicy imported from wrong module)
- Toolbar: removed redundant theme toggle button (menu bar item replaces it)
- Windows: switched PyInstaller build to onedir mode, eliminating the
  "Failed to remove temporary directory" warning popup on startup

===========================================================================
v20260419 (2026-04-19)
===========================================================================

New features
------------
- About dialog: toolbar '?' button shows the current version read from NEWS
- Tree view — collapsed by default: directories no longer expand automatically
  on load; users can expand only the folders they need
- Tree context menu: right-clicking a file node in the tree view now shows
  the same menu as the table view ('자세히', '가사보기', '재생목록에 추가',
  '인터넷에서 정보 보기', '태그 찾기')

Bug fixes / improvements
------------------------
- About dialog: fixed version showing "unknown" in packaged builds by bundling
  the NEWS file in PyInstaller specs (linux.spec and windows.spec)
- Windows MSI build: fixed codepage error by replacing Korean strings with
  English equivalents in installer.wxs
- Windows MSI build: fixed ICE50 validation error by removing Icon attribute
  from the desktop shortcut (exe embedded icon is used automatically)
- Windows MSI build: added LICENSE.rtf (required by WixUIExtension license
  screen); added build/make_license_rtf.py to regenerate it from LICENSE
- Windows MSI build: improved WiX Toolset v3 auto-detection in build_msi.ps1

===========================================================================
v20260409 (2026-04-09)
===========================================================================

New features
------------
- DB per directory: SQLite database is now stored inside the selected music
  directory as `.mp3-archive.db`; switching directories automatically opens
  (or creates) the corresponding DB and runs an incremental scan
- Album art tooltip: hovering over the album column shows the embedded album
  art of that track as a tooltip image
- Tag fetch — force mode: right-clicking a row and choosing "태그 찾기" now
  opens the tag-fetch dialog even for files that already have both title and
  artist tags
- Tag fetch — auto-retry: when a search returns no results the dialog
  automatically retries using the bare filename as the keyword before giving up
- Tag fetch — no-results popup: if both the initial search and the filename
  retry return no results a notification popup is shown to the user
- Playing-row highlight (dark theme): current track is now highlighted with a
  bright blue background and bold text so it is clearly visible in dark mode
- Windows MSI installer: `build/build_msi.ps1` + `build/installer.wxs` produce
  a signed-ready MSI via WiX Toolset v3; version is read from NEWS automatically
- Linux DEB package: `build/package_deb.sh` produces a dpkg-installable
  `.deb` file; version is read from NEWS automatically

Bug fixes / improvements
------------------------
- DEB runtime crash: switched PyInstaller Linux build to onedir mode with
  `noarchive=True` and `upx=False` to prevent `pyimod02_importers` /
  `ipaddress` import errors in the installed package
- Removed album art tooltip from the filename column (was confusing)
- requirements.txt: removed unused Pillow dependency; marked pyinstaller as
  build-only comment

===========================================================================
v20260407 (2026-04-07)
===========================================================================

New features
------------
- iTunes Search: tag-fetch dialog now supports iTunes Search API as an
  alternative source; source selector lets users choose MusicBrainz,
  iTunes, or both simultaneously; iTunes results show a "출처" (source)
  column; default source switched to iTunes for better Korean music coverage
- Album art panel: dedicated panel in the player area shows the embedded
  album art of the currently playing track; displays a '♪' placeholder
  when no art is embedded
- Playlist drag-and-drop reorder: items in the playlist can now be
  dragged to a new position; the playing index stays in sync after reorder

Bug fixes
---------
- Playlist reorder: items no longer disappear when dragged (Qt internal
  MIME type is now passed through the event filter correctly)
- Code: QIcon import moved to module level; removed redundant list_files()
  call in _fill_table when search count label is updated

